runs.comm: this was the bouncer, loopy bouncer rather, Finch swivels to pull but misses
looked a touch streaky at first, pitched up and it invites the lofted drive, just chipped over cover
skids through and hits his pads as he works it to the on side
drifts on the body and he shuffles and works it down to fine leg
swings it and it's full and thuds his pads as he tries to work it away, Best appeals but that was missing leg
134.2 kph, seemed quicker than that, he hops at the crease and steers it wide of point
chopped it on! Another flop for Finch, Sammy tucked him up for room, Finch was trying to cut, presumably, not the right shot for that ball, dragged it to the stumps
drifts on the body and he shuffles and works it to the on side
goes back at the crease and works it down to short fine leg
stays at the crease and works it away down to midwicket
good length on middle and leg and h swivels and mistimes the pull down to fine leg
stays on the back foot and he pushes it softly to the off side for a single
drifts it full and on the pads and he tries to whip it away but he fails to clip it away
this was short, Voges made room and clubs it in front of square over midwicket, clean strike
makes room and scoops a fullish delivery over extra cover, didn't quite time it as well
another fast, full delivery and he somehow drags it out to the on side
this was full and quick and on the pads and he mistimes it to the on side
fires this one wide down the leg side
slower ball and Voges drops it towards cover and he sets off for a quick single
he pulls a length ball over midwicket and Pollard jogs to his left at deep midwicket
much better shot, timed better and it goes quickly to Pollard at deep midwicket
good shot! This was short outside off he made room and slashed at it and it went in the air and just over Best at third man
backs away and cuts him down to backward point
swivels and pulls and well fielded by Charles at deep square leg
drifts down the leg side and wide called
slower ball on the pads and he works it down to long-on
full and bashed down the pitch and straight to the stumps at the other end
spins back in and he makes room and punches it to mid-off
chipped in the air just over Gayle at midwicket, cries of 'catch it'
this was short and he mistimes the pull down to long-on
stays back at the crease and makes room and cuts wide of point, three men chase after it! The Amazing race
stays back and he works it to the on side
stays back and tucks it away down to short fine leg
poor delivery, should have put that away, drifts down the leg side, he makes room and pulls and short fine leg fumbles
goes several rows back! This was short and he swiveled and clubbed it high and long over deep square leg
pushes it down to mid-off
works it away to deep midwicket
stays back and chops it down towards point
bowls it full outside off and he opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
makes room and thuds it down the track and Russell does well to deflect it away
makes room and chops it down to point, good restrictive line
pitched up on middle and leg and he makes room and swings it over deep midwicket, brings up the fifty stand!
makes room and Voges forces it away past the infield, Pollard's there at sweeper cover
fullish outside off and steered down to deep point
tossed up and he comes forward and drills a half volley down to long-off
comes round the wicket, he makes room and lofts against the turn over cover, Russell mops up
the reverse sweep this time, gets into position quickly and chips it over point
nicely controlled! Tossed up and Voges comes down the track and lofts it crisply over midwicket
overthrow! Voges chops it towards point, Best picks up and throws to the keeper Thomas who fumbles, nobody backing up
stays back and chops it towards cover point
comes round the wicket, he makes room and chops it down to cover
over the wicket to the left-hander and he drills it straight to cover
drifts on the body and he chips it towards mid-on
makes a bit of room and cuts him down to deep backward point
skids through on the pads and he stays back and works it to the on side
comes round the wicket, he makes room and bashes it down to long-on, lots of power behind that
chips down the track and he works it down to long-on and it's his fifty! Like Charles, Voges carrying on from the MCG
stays back and works it to the on side
goes back at the crease and cuts him to sweeper cover

there's an appeal for the run-out and this looked quite close! Goes back and chops it down to point, Voges sets off, Best fires a flat throw to Thomas and Marsh is just short of his ground, top stuff from West Indies
confident way to get off the mark, on his knee and sweeps firmly to deep square leg
stays at the crease, bends and pulls it to deep square leg
we have another run out here! Slower ball, Bailey tries to work it away but misses, they try to sneak in a bye, Thomas hits the stumps and Voges is well short, it was evident even at normal speed
gets off the mark with a chop wide of backward point
Bailey goes for the loft and he just about manages to clear the fielder, Russell chases at long-off
goes for the wild slog and some luck goes Bailey's way as the outside edge sails towards third man and rolls to the rope
nothing streaky about this one! Pitched up and he connects well with the slog, races to deep midwicket
stays back at the crease and chops it wide of cover
spins back in as he tries to work it away, hits the pads and rolls away
works it down to deep square leg
goes back and steers it to backward point
the captain goes and Australia are losing the plot! Bailey was down on his knee to sweep and he gets a top edge towards short square leg, Deonarine times his dive well and takes the catch
stays back and clips it to deep square leg
slower ball and he works it softly towards the on side and Pollard darts across and cuts it off but can't cut off the single
slower ball and he drills it back to the bowler
drifts on the pads and he clips it away towards short fine leg
good delivery, slower ball and a tight line, no room to work with and he softly pushes it down the track
goes back at the crease and punches a slower delivery to sweeper cover
this was quicker, shorter and it fizzed past the outside edge and Thomas took it high on the gloves
they need more of those! Flatter one and Haddin stays at the crease, leans forward and swings it over long-on
6 + 4! Short one from Deonarine, poor ball, Haddin was down on his knee and pounded that over square leg
add another 6! Could this be the over? Tossed up on middle and leg and he gets on his knee and slogs him clean down to deep midwicket, a few rows back
no boundary this time so relief for WI, drills it down the ground to long-on
goes back at the crease and pushes it wide of cover
chops it down to short third man and that ends a very expensive over - 21
on the pads and he whips it away wide of midwicket
the slower bouncer and he makes room and tries to slash it, the ball passes the edge

Russell takes a very sharp catch and celebrates with the Gangnam Style! It was looped up on the off stump, Haddin made room and bashed it flat, it really rocketed off the bat and Russell was alert at long-off, got across to the right quickly and plucked it, hung on to it on the dive
stays back and pushes it down to sweeper cover for a couple
effortless! This was pitched up on the off stump, looked to push that down the ground and ended up middling it so well that it carried all the way over long-off
pushes it to short third man
tries to work it to the on side and he mistimes it
this was short and he goes back and clubs it down to deep midwicket
works it just wide of the bowler on the on side
drags it short and he swivels and mistimes it wide of short fine leg
worked away to the on side and Faulkner set off for the second but was wisely sent back, how many run-outs can they afford?
tucked away behind square on the on side
slower ball and he pretty much flat-bats it down to long-on
Sammy takes it! This was slower and fuller, Faulkner tries to launch it over long-on, it dips towards Sammy who takes it well in front of the rope, starts off the Gangnam but changes his mind
two in two! Another slower ball, this was short, Rohrer moved right across his stumps and tried to pull it behind square on the on side, finds short fine leg
short ball and it fizzes up and he swings and misses
Dropped! Could have been three for the over, he swings and gets a huge top edge, miles in the air, Sammy and Dwayne B converge, Bravo messes up, Sammy sees the lighter side to it
all too easy for Thomas! Tossed up and he was down the track to launch it, beaten for turn too, doesn't bother scampering back
fullish on the off stump and clipped away down to long-on
flatter delivery and he slogs it away and it's along the ground to deep midwicket
punches it down the ground to long-on
makes room to bash that through the off side and he misses
goes back at the crease and pushes it towards extra cover
the slower ball and he goes for the slog and misses it completely
another swing and a miss, good change of pace again
he swishes at thin air again, this looks like a hopelessly lost cause for Australia
four consecutive dot balls! Coulter Nile is having a horror game with the bat, slower ball, swings and misses
connects finally! The length was getting predictable, he stayed back and clubbed it over deep midwicket
back to back sixes! Funny old over, short and he stays back and connects well again over deep midwicket. If only he connected the first four balls just as well
fires that full and he digs it out down to mid-off and sets off, the throw to the keeper was a bit wide
this was a really quick bouncer and inches over the helmet, Reiffel calls it a wide
makes room and gets an under edge to the keeper, they scamper the single
Dropped. shouldn't really matter at this stage, makes room and tries to clear midwicket, Narine runs back and spills it
down the leg side and nearly clips the pads as he tries to clip it away
moves right across and tries to pull and the ball hits the pads and dribbles away
full toss to end the game, it was quick and towards the pads and McKay made room and failed to connect, eye contact between the batsman and bowler but they shake hands, they're laughing about it now
